io.github.anagalacticruby

Class Widget

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.anagalacticruby.Product
      • io.github.anagalacticruby.Widget
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Item

    class Widget
extends Product
    This class is to make sure the product class works.

    The widget class is also how the program is able to add Products to the TableView in the Product Line tab. Why? Because the Product class is abstract, and we cannot make instances of an abstract class. However we can make instances of subclasses that extend an abstract class.

      • Widget

        Widget(java.lang.String name,
       java.lang.String manufacturer,
       ItemType type)
        A constructor for Widgets which also happen to be Products.

        It takes the same values of a Product (name,manufacturer,ItemType), allowing users to create Widget Objects. The fact that it takes the same parameters as a Product allows the program to store them in an ObservableList (See the controller), and do other things that Products would normally be required for. This is because of inheritance and Polymorphism.

        Parameters:
        name - The name of the widget (Effectively a Product name)
        manufacturer - The manufacturer of the Widget (Product manufacturer)
        type - The ItemType of the Widget (Product Type)
